  <brief_title>A Study Comparing Continuous Subcutaneous Insulin Infusion With Multiple Daily Injections With Insulin Lispro and Glargine</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Study Comparing Continuous Subcutaneous Insulin Infusion With Multiple Daily Injections With Insulin Lispro and Glargine</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hoffmann-La Roche</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hoffmann-La Roche</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This trial will compare the metabolic control in type 1 diabetes obtained by continuous
      infusion of insulin lispro with that obtained by multiple daily injections of insulin lispro
      and glargine, a long-acting insulin analogue. Patients will be switched to the alternative
      treatment after 4 months. Glucose variability in the last month of each treatment will be
      analyzed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
